{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay"]}],"metadata":{"title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"},{"kind":"text","text":" <"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","text":"MLNAnnotation","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(pl)MLNAnnotation"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You use overlays to layer more sophisticated content on top of a map view. For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, you could use an overlay to show the boundaries of a national park or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trace a bus route along city streets. This SDK defines several concrete classes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that conform to this protocol and define standard shapes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"],"title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"title":"MLNMultiPolyline","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/coordinate":{"title":"coordinate","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/coordinate","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"coordinate"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A coordinate representing the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolyline":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolyline","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolyline","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"text":" instances, and the line segments that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"path along which something moves.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNPolygon","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","title":"MapLibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","role":"symbol","title":"overlayBounds","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"title":"MLNPointCollection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disconnected vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/intersectsOverlayBounds:":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"intersectsOverlayBounds:"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Returns a Boolean indicating whether the specified rectangle intersects the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"receiver’s shape.","type":"text"}],"title":"intersectsOverlayBounds:","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/intersectsoverlaybounds:","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/intersectsOverlayBounds:"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolygon":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygons that do not overlap. For example, you could use a multipolygon shape"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to represent the body of land that consists of an island surrounded by an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll: the inner island would be one "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object, while the surrounding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"atoll would be another. You could also use a multipolygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group of disconnected but related buildings."}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNMultiPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNMultiPolygon","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolygon","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"}}}